                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-186" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN ALTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Francis Cotton, pawnbroker, Hackney-road. In consequence of information I received, I ran out of the shop on the morning of the 29th of October, and saw the prisoner going up Wey<lb></lb>mouth-terrace—he was walking, but when he heard me coming he ran—I called "Stop thief"—he threw a handkerchief from his jacket, which I picked up—I ran after him, and a man stopped him—I took him back to the policeman and gave him into custody—the handkerchief belongs to Mr. Cotton—it is silk—it had been pawned, and was not redeemed.</p>
